21	-- ``AW`` transactions are queued up while other ``W`` and ``B`` transactions are running,
22	-- and further ``W`` transactions are performed while waiting for other ``B`` transactions.
23	--
24	-- Arbitration is done in simplest most resource-efficient manner possible, which
25	-- means that one input port can block others if it continuously sends transactions.
